{"title": "New Publication: Beyond false balance", "author": "Climate Matters Editorial Team", "url": "https://climatematters.blogs.uni-hamburg.de/2017/01/new-publication-beyond-false-balance/", "hostname": "uni-hamburg.de", "description": "Finally, the article \u201eBeyond false balance: How interpretive journalism shapes media coverage of climate change\u201d is available online. The article is an outcome of our project \u201cFraming Climate Change\u201d and was published by the journal Global Environmental Change. The article explores the framing of", "sitename": "Climate Matters", "date": "2017-01-03", "id": null, "license": null, "body": null, "comments": "", "commentsbody": null, "raw_text": null, "text": "Finally, the article \u201eBeyond false balance: How interpretive journalism shapes media coverage of climate change\u201d is available online. The article is an outcome of our project \u201c\n[Framing Climate Change](https://climatematters.blogs.uni-hamburg.de/framing-climate-change/)\u201d and was published by the journal Global Environmental Change.\nThe article explores the framing of climate change as a harmful, human-induced risk and the way that reporting handles contrarian voices in the climate debate. The analysis shows how journalists, and their interpretations and professional norms, shape media debates about climate change. The study links an analysis of media content to a survey of the authors of the respective articles. It covers leading print and online news outlets in Germany, India, the United Kingdom, the United States, and Switzerland and finds that climate journalism has moved beyond the norm of balance towards a more interpretive pattern of journalism. Quoting contrarian voices still is part of transnational climate coverage, but these quotes are contextualized with a dismissal of climate change denial. Yet niches of denial persist in certain contexts, and much journalistic attention is focused on the narrative of \u2018warners vs. deniers,\u2019 and overlooks the more relevant debates about climate change.\nFree access to the article is available until February 18th 2017 via\n[this link. ](https://authors.elsevier.com/a/1UIrQ3Q8oPtW0v)Afterwards, the article will be available [here](http://dx.doi.org/10.1016/j.gloenvcha.2016.11.004).\nEine Zusammenfassung des Artikels auf Deutsch gibt es auf\n[klimafakten.de](https://www.klimafakten.de/meldung/journalismus-die-zeiten-ausgewogener-berichterstattung-zwischen-wissenschaft-und)", "language": null, "image": "https://climatematters.blogs.uni-hamburg.de/wp-content/uploads/2020/11/pexels-akil-mazumder-1072824-scaled.jpg", "pagetype": "article", "links": ["#site-navigation", "#content", "https://climatematters.blogs.uni-hamburg.de/", "https://climatematters.blogs.uni-hamburg.de/?taxonomy=nav_menu&term=categories", "https://climatematters.blogs.uni-hamburg.de/category/media-politics/", "https://climatematters.blogs.uni-hamburg.de/category/research/", "https://climatematters.blogs.uni-hamburg.de/category/wider-debate/", "https://climatematters.blogs.uni-hamburg.de/about-us/team/", "https://climatematters.blogs.uni-hamburg.de/media-watch-blog/about-our-blog/", "https://climatematters.blogs.uni-hamburg.de/about-us/team/", "https://climatematters.blogs.uni-hamburg.de/about-us/media-watch-bloggers/", "https://climatematters.blogs.uni-hamburg.de/about-us/projects/", "https://climatematters.blogs.uni-hamburg.de/impressum/", "https://climatematters.blogs.uni-hamburg.de/climate-change-the-basics/", "https://climatematters.blogs.uni-hamburg.de/?taxonomy=nav_menu&term=categories", "https://climatematters.blogs.uni-hamburg.de/category/media-politics/", "https://climatematters.blogs.uni-hamburg.de/category/research/", "https://climatematters.blogs.uni-hamburg.de/category/wider-debate/", "https://climatematters.blogs.uni-hamburg.de/about-us/team/", "https://climatematters.blogs.uni-hamburg.de/media-watch-blog/about-our-blog/", "https://climatematters.blogs.uni-hamburg.de